The app has no body parser or input validation. For any POST/PUT routes added later:
```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' })); // Limit body size to prevent large payload attacks
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false }));
```

### 4. ❌ Error Handling Middleware (Medium Priority)
There's no centralized error handler. Unhandled errors can leak stack traces:
```js
// Catch-all 404 handler
app.use((req, res) => {
  res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not Found' });
});

// Global error handler
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // Log internally, not to client
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' });
});
```

### 5. 🌐 CORS Configuration (Medium Priority)
The app doesn't configure CORS, which defaults to allowing all origins:
```js
